cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.MM 

The paper is about developing and validating a deep learning algorithm to predict the progression of age-related macular degeneration from fundus images. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques for analyzing the images, machine learning (ML) algorithms for predicting the progression, and artificial intelligence (AI) methods for training the DL algorithm. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential clinical applications of the DL algorithm, which could involve human-computer interaction (HC) and multimedia (MM) technologies. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The less likely but still possible sub-categories are cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
